Uh...

14:54.341 --> 14:56.424
Mm, that's unfortunate.

14:56.508 --> 14:59.508
Um, look,
Mr. Pickles...

14:59.591 --> 15:01.257
here's the thing.

15:01.341 --> 15:03.924
Can I tell you what I think
really happened?

15:04.007 --> 15:06.132
I-I don't think
that your phone is broken.

15:06.216 --> 15:08.965
I think that, uh, it's hers
that's broken,

15:09.049 --> 15:12.090
and that's why
she's not responding.

15:12.174 --> 15:14.132
[chuckles]
That makes sense.

15:14.216 --> 15:15.965
I knew there was a reason
I brought you.

15:16.049 --> 15:17.882
[chuckles]
He's the family computer whiz.

15:17.965 --> 15:19.758
[chuckles]
Yeah, that's...

15:19.840 --> 15:22.007
Uh, so is there anything else
I can help you with?

15:22.090 --> 15:23.216
Just that.

15:23.299 --> 15:26.299
♪ somber music ♪

15:26.382 --> 15:28.716
♪♪♪

15:28.799 --> 15:31.924
[Scott] Once upon a time,
there was a swing in a branch

15:32.007 --> 15:34.965
and a big, fat marshmallow.

15:35.049 --> 15:37.633
[Maddy] Why does the cat
only eat marshmallows, Dad?

15:37.716 --> 15:39.633
Why do you think?
Turn the page.

15:39.716 --> 15:40.799
[laughs]

15:40.882 --> 15:43.758
[laughing]
I only see the cat!

15:43.840 --> 15:45.758
[Maddy]
The kitty's so dismay-ded,

15:45.840 --> 15:47.965
but there's a marshmallow,
and the kitty's like...

15:48.049 --> 15:49.382
♪♪♪

15:49.466 --> 15:51.216
I'm sick.

15:51.299 --> 15:52.382
So breathe that way.

15:52.466 --> 15:54.216
I'm not sleeping
on the fold-out.

15:54.299 --> 15:56.216
No, I mean I'm sick, Dee Dee.

15:56.299 --> 15:58.424
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

16:01.216 --> 16:02.799
I need...

16:05.549 --> 16:07.674
Oh, God, I've pictured having
this conversation

16:07.799 --> 16:09.007
since I was 13,

16:09.090 --> 16:11.840
and now I don't know
how to start it.

16:14.674 --> 16:16.466
But...

16:19.216 --> 16:20.924
...a word that's...

16:21.007 --> 16:24.007
defined me for a while
has been...

16:26.257 --> 16:28.007
...confusion.

16:30.591 --> 16:32.090
[sighs]

16:32.174 --> 16:35.299
[cries]

16:37.716 --> 16:40.216
[crying] Even ten words in,
it already feels

16:40.299 --> 16:42.341
so cathartic...

16:42.424 --> 16:45.341
[sighs]
...to open up...

16:45.424 --> 16:48.257
about what I'm trying
to say, baby.

16:48.341 --> 16:49.758
[sniffles]

16:49.840 --> 16:51.799
♪ quiet orchestral music ♪

16:51.882 --> 16:55.965
In the deepest part
of myself...

16:56.049 --> 16:58.049
♪♪♪

16:58.132 --> 16:59.799
...I've always--

16:59.882 --> 17:02.799
Name a happy child
of divorce.

17:02.882 --> 17:05.799
♪♪♪

17:05.882 --> 17:06.965
What?

17:07.049 --> 17:09.840
Name one happy child
of divorce.

17:09.924 --> 17:12.424
Can I finish
what I'm trying to say?

17:12.508 --> 17:15.007
Oh...

17:15.090 --> 17:18.382
the Tooth Fairy
needs to find her wand.

17:18.466 --> 17:23.049
♪♪♪

17:23.132 --> 17:24.382
[door opens]

17:24.466 --> 17:29.382
♪♪♪

17:36.758 --> 17:38.257
[whispering]
Where do your teeth go?

17:38.341 --> 17:40.341
♪♪♪

17:40.424 --> 17:41.758
Hi, Mom.

17:41.840 --> 17:43.382
[raspy voice]
I'm Mr. Chompers.

17:43.466 --> 17:45.174
Jesus! Fuck!

17:45.257 --> 17:48.174
And I eat dreams.
Nom! Nom!

17:48.257 --> 17:50.674
Nom...

17:50.758 --> 17:53.424
♪ spacey melancholy music ♪

17:53.508 --> 17:58.591
♪♪♪

18:32.549 --> 18:34.549
I'm sorry.

18:36.216 --> 18:38.633
I don't even know
how to talk to you anymore,

18:38.716 --> 18:41.549
but I want you to know that...

18:41.633 --> 18:44.007
I do it all the time
in my head,

18:44.090 --> 18:47.758
so it feels like I talk to you
more than I do.

18:47.840 --> 18:52.174
♪ dark music ♪

18:52.257 --> 18:55.549
I'm always asking myself
if I'm trying too hard.

18:55.633 --> 18:57.882
Am I?

18:57.965 --> 19:00.132
Or not enough?

19:00.216 --> 19:01.882
♪♪♪

19:01.965 --> 19:04.382
I used to be so good
at putting myself

19:04.466 --> 19:06.633
between you and...

19:06.716 --> 19:10.216
anything that tried
to hurt you, but...

19:10.299 --> 19:13.007
I couldn't...

19:13.090 --> 19:15.758
I couldn't put myself
between you and what happened.

19:15.840 --> 19:17.591
I...

19:17.674 --> 19:20.840
I couldn't stop...

19:20.924 --> 19:23.508
you losing everything.

19:23.591 --> 19:25.508
♪♪♪

19:25.591 --> 19:28.508
And...

19:28.591 --> 19:30.840
I don't know how
to protect you anymore,

19:30.924 --> 19:33.674
and maybe I shouldn't.

19:33.758 --> 19:36.382
Maybe that's how I help.

19:36.466 --> 19:41.633
♪♪♪

19:48.965 --> 19:52.466
Have you ever seen
the movie Robocop?

19:52.549 --> 19:53.840
Maybe?

19:53.924 --> 19:55.216
It's about a police officer

19:55.299 --> 19:57.216
who dies
in the line of duty.

19:57.299 --> 20:00.174
His buddies rebuild him
like a robot

20:00.257 --> 20:02.424
so they can control him,

20:02.508 --> 20:04.591
but he just gets...

20:04.674 --> 20:06.965
way more violent.

20:07.049 --> 20:08.549
♪♪♪

20:13.633 --> 20:16.716
[knock at door]

20:16.799 --> 20:18.716
Just a sec.

20:22.424 --> 20:25.549
[sighs]

20:27.924 --> 20:30.466
Hi.

20:30.549 --> 20:32.549
I didn't know
you were coming.

20:35.508 --> 20:39.257
Welcome to my...
home away from home.

20:41.382 --> 20:44.758
[door closes]

20:44.840 --> 20:46.508
What happened here?

20:46.591 --> 20:47.633
Um...

20:47.716 --> 20:50.341
a lamp got broken.

20:50.424 --> 20:52.424
And you're sleeping
on a futon?

20:52.508 --> 20:56.299
Yeah, sometimes I want a bed.
Sometimes I want a couch.

20:56.382 --> 20:59.799
It's Spartan,
but it's everything I need.

20:59.882 --> 21:01.132
Where does Will sleep?

21:01.216 --> 21:04.549
Oh, I have
an inflatable mattress.

21:04.633 --> 21:07.424
He thinks it's like
a water bed, only with air.

21:07.508 --> 21:10.132
You could be in a suite
at the Four Seasons, Jeff.

21:10.216 --> 21:12.049
I'm happy here.

21:12.132 --> 21:14.466
What you don't see
are the memories.

21:14.549 --> 21:16.466
My first apartment...

21:16.549 --> 21:19.090
short stroll
right across campus.

21:19.174 --> 21:21.174
Before I say
what I'm going to say,

21:21.257 --> 21:22.508
you should know
that your son was very touched

21:22.591 --> 21:24.174
by what you did.

21:24.257 --> 21:26.257
[inhales deeply]
I didn't expect that.

21:26.341 --> 21:27.633
We raised a good boy.

21:27.716 --> 21:30.299
But the guilt that I felt

21:30.382 --> 21:33.049
for wanting a sixth pair
of shoes...

21:33.132 --> 21:34.466
Who said
you couldn't have shoes?

21:34.549 --> 21:36.049
...or a car
that's just fun...

21:36.132 --> 21:37.758
- It's a lot of shoes.
- ...and fast to drive...

21:37.840 --> 21:39.341
You want another car?
Get another car.

21:39.424 --> 21:40.799
- ...or for hating the man...
- Get six cars--

21:40.882 --> 21:42.299
one for every day
of the week.

21:42.382 --> 21:44.132
...who drove a snack truck
into our family,

21:44.216 --> 21:45.882
and meanwhile, you are writing
checks for his rent,

21:45.965 --> 21:47.591
his utility bills?

21:47.674 --> 21:50.341
You're paying
his garbage pickup?

21:53.216 --> 21:55.341
He has a daughter.

21:57.216 --> 21:59.799
Someday she's gonna have
to go to college.

22:01.965 --> 22:04.924
[crying]
We had a son,

22:05.007 --> 22:06.924
and he will never go
to college!

22:07.007 --> 22:08.924
Denny hurt his back
in the accident.

22:09.007 --> 22:11.382
- Denny?
- He walks with a cane now.

22:11.466 --> 22:14.090
Of course you're
on a first-name basis with him!

22:14.174 --> 22:16.466
Did you not think
how giving that man money

22:16.549 --> 22:17.674
would make me feel?

22:17.758 --> 22:19.341
He can't drive anymore.

22:19.424 --> 22:20.882
Workmen's compensation
won't cover the cost

22:20.965 --> 22:22.549
of a single-parent household.

22:22.633 --> 22:25.007
Someone has
to look out for him.

22:25.090 --> 22:28.299
We weren't the only ones
who lost something.

22:28.382 --> 22:30.591
We're the only ones
that matter.

22:30.674 --> 22:32.840
I devoted an entire show
to Phil's death...

22:32.924 --> 22:35.341
- [sighs]
- ...an honest show.

22:35.424 --> 22:37.090
They're gonna air it soon.

22:37.174 --> 22:40.049
I don't watch
Puppet Time  anymore.

22:40.132 --> 22:43.591
Watching it makes me
want to swallow my tongue.

22:43.674 --> 22:45.758
You shouldn't blame that man
for what happened.

22:45.840 --> 22:47.674
I don't blame him.

22:47.758 --> 22:50.049
I hate him.

22:50.132 --> 22:52.132
I blame myself
for what happened.

22:52.216 --> 22:54.132
It was an accident--

22:54.216 --> 22:56.965
a stray burst of electrons
through a stoplight.

22:57.049 --> 23:00.007
- A broken lamp.
- An act of God.

23:00.090 --> 23:02.758
He's not the bad guy.

23:02.840 --> 23:04.549
Neither are you, Jill.

23:06.341 --> 23:08.591
- No one is.
- That's what you don't get.

23:08.674 --> 23:11.965
Next to you, I am the bad guy.

23:12.049 --> 23:14.174
I always am.

23:14.257 --> 23:17.174
No, you're a wonderful person,
and I miss you

23:17.257 --> 23:18.674
- more than anything.
- Don't.

23:18.758 --> 23:23.090
[sobbing]

23:23.174 --> 23:25.674
Oh, I loved you, Jeff,

23:25.758 --> 23:27.424
but...

23:28.840 --> 23:33.633
...after the accident,
when all the cards arrived...

23:33.716 --> 23:36.049
they were all addressed
to you.

23:36.132 --> 23:38.591
They were meant
for both of us.

23:38.674 --> 23:41.132
You're Santa.

23:41.216 --> 23:43.591
I'm Mrs. Claus.

23:43.674 --> 23:45.382
Santa brings joy.

23:45.466 --> 23:47.466
Mrs. Claus brings...

23:47.549 --> 23:50.382
kibble to the reindeer.

23:52.049 --> 23:54.382
Well, I don't live
on the North Pole anymore.

23:54.466 --> 23:58.090
[sniffles]
I live in reality now.

23:58.174 --> 24:00.882
It's not as colorful, but...

24:00.965 --> 24:03.965
I see the world
how it really is.

24:04.049 --> 24:07.007
The world
is a perfect circle...

24:07.090 --> 24:09.424
of endless possibilities.

24:11.090 --> 24:14.090
It's not a circle.

24:14.174 --> 24:16.424
It's a hole.

24:18.007 --> 24:20.716
♪ disquieting
percussive music ♪

24:20.799 --> 24:24.090
♪♪♪

24:24.174 --> 24:26.466
That truck driver...

24:26.549 --> 24:28.591
♪♪♪

24:28.674 --> 24:31.758
He didn't hurt his back
in the accident.

24:31.840 --> 24:33.965
Maybe he told you he did,

24:34.049 --> 24:36.174
but that is called a lie.

24:36.257 --> 24:38.341
He just wants
your money.

24:38.424 --> 24:40.508
He's stealing from you,

24:40.591 --> 24:42.466
and teaching Will
a magic trick

24:42.549 --> 24:44.299
isn't gonna get him
to stop smoking pot.

24:44.382 --> 24:47.216
And when you screw a woman
you just met

24:47.299 --> 24:49.007
and she doesn't call you back,

24:49.090 --> 24:51.341
it's not 'cause her phone
is broken.

24:51.424 --> 24:54.257
It's 'cause
she doesn't like you!

24:54.341 --> 24:58.049
I'm sorry,
but this is where we live.

24:58.132 --> 25:01.840
Please, join us.

25:01.924 --> 25:06.382
♪♪♪

25:06.466 --> 25:08.758
[door closes]

25:08.840 --> 25:10.882
[sniffles]

25:10.965 --> 25:13.799
♪♪♪

25:13.882 --> 25:16.799
[rumbling]

25:16.882 --> 25:21.549
♪♪♪

25:21.633 --> 25:23.882
[cell phone plays
"Shave and a Haircut"]

25:23.965 --> 25:29.049
♪♪♪

25:43.174 --> 25:44.882
[chuckles]

25:44.965 --> 25:47.882
♪ whistling jaunty tune ♪

25:47.965 --> 25:48.840
♪♪♪

25:48.924 --> 25:51.924
♪ soft music ♪

25:52.007 --> 25:56.799
♪♪♪

25:56.882 --> 25:59.924
♪ whistling jaunty tune ♪

26:00.007 --> 26:03.049
♪♪♪

26:03.132 --> 26:05.840
♪ soft music continues ♪

26:05.924 --> 26:09.382
♪♪♪

26:09.466 --> 26:12.007
Is it the... queen of hearts?

26:12.090 --> 26:13.840
♪♪♪

26:13.924 --> 26:16.007
[sighs]

26:16.090 --> 26:17.341
No way!

26:17.424 --> 26:18.633
[laughs]

26:18.716 --> 26:21.591
♪ whistling jaunty tune ♪

26:21.674 --> 26:26.591
♪♪♪

26:39.132 --> 26:40.299
Mom?

26:40.382 --> 26:45.466
♪♪♪

27:01.049 --> 27:03.090
[dog barks]

27:03.174 --> 27:07.049
♪ soft music continues ♪

27:07.132 --> 27:09.299
Isn't it amazing, Gertie?

27:09.382 --> 27:14.466
♪♪♪

27:19.132 --> 27:22.007
♪ Adrian Younge's
"Stranger by the Sea" ♪

27:22.090 --> 27:26.299
♪♪♪

27:26.382 --> 27:31.299
♪ A stranger landed
from the sea ♪

27:31.382 --> 27:35.508
♪ I welcomed him
to come to me ♪

27:35.591 --> 27:40.090
♪♪♪

27:40.174 --> 27:45.007
♪ We touched
but he swam back to sea ♪

27:47.007 --> 27:51.840
♪ He saw the cold and misery ♪

27:53.799 --> 27:56.924
♪ He sails the seven oceans ♪

27:57.007 --> 28:00.508
♪ Exploring his emotions ♪
